paragraph.content:
compensation in respect of damage arising from contamination caused by the
          discharge or escape of bunker oil from ships or in respect of a threat of such
          damage;

in relation to an application for an insurance certificate to be issued
                        by an authorized person, the fee determined by the person under section
                            25(3);

subsection.def:
damage
                    (損害) includes loss, but does not include loss
                of life or personal injury;

paragraph.content:
if the incident causes any relevant threat of contamination to occur,
                        any reasonable measures taken by a person to prevent or minimize any damage
                        caused outside a ship by contamination that might result if there were a
                        discharge or escape of bunker oil from the ship;

in any other case, the person registered as the owner of the ship or,
                        if no person is registered as the owner of the ship, the person who owns the
                        ship;

subsection.def:
ship
                    (船舶) means a sea-going vessel or seaborne
                craft of any type;

subparagraph.content:
the shipowner of the ship at the time of the occurrence resulting in
                        the discharge or escape;
                        or

section.def:
e-cert database (電子證書資料庫), in relation to an issuing authority, means an electronic database
            that is maintained or managed by or for the issuing authority in accordance with the
            e-cert guidelines;

paragraph.content:
request the master of a ship to which Part 3 applies to produce
                    for the officer’s inspection the insurance certificate or the specified
                    certificate relating to the ship;

request the master of a ship to produce for the officer’s inspection any
                    other document relating to the ship and to provide any information relating to
                    the ship;
